Source: duckbotos-kiosk
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: DuckBotOS Team <duckets@duckbotos.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: duckbotos-kiosk
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: weston (>= 13),
         xwayland,
         chromium-browser | chromium | google-chrome,
         xdg-utils,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Weston kiosk shell + Chromium for DuckBotOS agent desktop
 This package provides the fullscreen kiosk experience that makes
 DuckBotOS an "agent-first OS."
 .
 What it does:
 - Starts Weston as a Wayland compositor in kiosk mode
 - Launches Chromium in fullscreen app mode (--kiosk --noerrdialogs)
 - Points Chromium at the agent's web dashboard URL
 - Handles display switching, idle timeout, power management
 .
 The URL loaded depends on /etc/duckbotos/kiosk-mode (set by
 duckbotos-kiosk-hermes, duckbotos-kiosk-openclaw, or
 duckbotos-session-picker at boot time).
 .
 Users cannot exit the kiosk (no taskbar, no alt-tab, no desktop).
 The only way out is via agent command or Ctrl+Alt+Backspace.
 .
 This is what makes DuckBotOS fundamentally different from a
 "desktop with an agent app" — the agent IS the entire display.
